result.execSummary:
The defendant Josef K Eibl was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Felony [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by each counsel, the defendant and Gerda Z.
  
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 72 MONTHS, consecutive, with credit for 91 DAYS time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 36 MONTHS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 36 MONTHS. 
The Court STAYED this sentence and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 4 YEARS, concurrent with case 15CF5339,  with the following conditions:
 *  Successfully complete any counseling and/or
         treatment deemed appropriate.
     *  Defendant to participate in a Mental Health Assessment and cooperate with any treatment.
     *  Defendant to have no contact with the victim unless approved by the court.
     *  Defendant to pay all applicable costs and surcharges, including the DV and DNA surcharges and his 
        supervision fees, bail on deposit to apply,  25% of his prison funds to apply for remaining fees, remainder to be paid during his period of extended supervision; failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.
     *  No contact with firearms.
     *  The Court advises the defendant that voting privileges are suspended during the length of this sentence. 
         Ineligible Voting Notice & Acknowledgment signed by the defendant and filed.  
     *  Provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank and pay all appropriate costs, pursuant to 973.047 of Wisconsin 
        statutes.
